Source: libauthen-nzrealme-perl
Section: perl
Priority: optional
Build-Depends: debhelper (>= 5)
Build-Depends-Indep: perl (>= 5.6.10-12)
Maintainer: Andrew Maguire <andrew.maguire@catalyst.net.nz>
Standards-Version: 3.8.0
Homepage: http://search.cpan.org/dist/Authen-NZRealMe/

Package: libauthen-nzrealme-perl
Architecture: all
Depends: ${perl:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}, openssl, zip, libxml-generator-perl, libxml-libxml-perl, liburi-perl, libwww-perl, libwww-curl-perl, libcrypt-openssl-rsa-perl, libcrypt-openssl-x509-perl, libio-compress-zlib-perl, libterm-readline-gnu-perl, libtimedate-perl, libossp-uuid-perl, libcryptx-perl, libjson-xs-perl
Description:  Tools for integrating with the New Zealand RealMe login and
 identity services (formerly "igovt logon").  This module provides an API for
 integrating your application with the New Zealand RealMe services using SAML
 2.0 messaging.
 .
 The distribution also includes a command-line tool called 'nzrealme' which can
 be used for generating certificates and metadata; generating authentication
 request messages and resolving artifacts.
